From c93bcb01dbc8d4665cf22e0c051f11e65c4da520 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Samuel <eunseobchoi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 09:27:42 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Keep submission tests from overriding scenario contracts

Submission verification and measurement must treat scenario-owned cape-tests.json files as the benchmark contract. A submission-local cape-tests.json now fails fast instead of replacing the trusted scenario tests, and the regression suite covers the rejection before the evaluator can run.

Constraint: GHSA-4rp3-v4vj-q537 reports that evaluatee-supplied tests can bias verification and benchmark results

Rejected: Silently ignore submission-local cape-tests.json | anomalous files would remain accepted in submissions and keep confusing reviewers

Confidence: high

Scope-risk: moderate

Directive: Do not reintroduce submission-local test overrides; add trusted scenario-level fixtures instead

Tested: git diff --check

Tested: bash -n scripts/lib/cape_common.sh scripts/cape-subcommands/submission/verify.sh scripts/cape-subcommands/submission/measure.sh scripts/cape-subcommands/test/test.sh

Tested: Stubbed verify/measure regression rejects submission-local cape-tests.json before invoking measure

Tested: Stubbed successful verify path passes scenarios/fibonacci/cape-tests.json to measure

Not-tested: Full cabal test suite; cabal and check-jsonschema are not installed in this environment
---
 .../cape-subcommands/submission/measure.sh    | 40 ++++++-----
 scripts/cape-subcommands/submission/verify.sh | 35 +++++-----
 scripts/cape-subcommands/test/test.sh         | 70 +++++++++++++++++++
 scripts/lib/cape_common.sh                    | 13 ++++
 4 files changed, 120 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)

